# 🧩 Component Structure

The project follows a modular component architecture with several types of components.

## 🔄 Component Types
- **Layout Components** - Components used for the page layout (header, footer, etc.)
- **UI Components** - Reusable UI elements (buttons, inputs, cards, etc.)
- **Page Components** - Components specific to individual pages
- **Common Components** - Shared components used across multiple pages

## 📂 Component Directories
- [src/components/layout](mdc:src/components/layout) - Layout components
- [src/components/ui](mdc:src/components/ui) - UI components using shadcn/ui
- [src/components/homePage](mdc:src/components/homePage) - Homepage-specific components
- [src/components/pagesComponent](mdc:src/components/pagesComponent) - Page-specific components
- [src/components/commonComponents](mdc:src/components/commonComponents) - Common components

## 📏 Component Conventions
- Components should be focused and not exceed 200 lines of code
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Follow the naming convention of PascalCase for component files
- Prefer functional components with hooks over class components
- Use proper commenting for complex logic
